modules.description: Provides time manipulation functions such as adding durations to timestamps, calculating time differences, and formatting time values. Works with custom time types including timestamps, durations, and time zones. Used to implement precise time-based logic in scheduling systems and log analysis tools.

Provides functions to retrieve and manipulate time values from various system clocks, including real-time, monotonic, and CPU-specific clocks. Operates on `clockid` values, which are integers representing different clock sources. Used for precise time measurement in applications requiring system time, process execution time, or thread-specific timing.
